      "post_id" : 29363433,
      "comment_id" : 47071750,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "For the compiler?  The compiler doesn&#39;t care other than to issue warnings to the developer, so they&#39;re both for the developer.  It&#39;s just that the annotation is nearly useless by itself, while the javadoc comment is not guaranteed to be used.  So Sun/Oracle (I don&#39;t know whose watch this was on) set up a situation where developers have to do two different things to adequately document the situation when one should have been sufficient."
